<p>
<seg id=1> International supervisory personnel stationed in Kosovo still have some hope that a ceasefire can be restored, despite several days of continuous fighting between Serbian security forces and Albanian separatists. </seg>
<seg id=2> A spokesperson for the supervisory personnel indicated on Monday at Pristina that the situation in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo is currently calm. </seg>
<seg id=3> At least 12 persons died in the fighting last week. </seg>
<seg id=4> The Polish chairman of the European Safety and Cooperation Organization, Gaiermeike, accused both sides in the fight of causing the current violent confrontation. </seg>
</p>
